I know I’ve had moments of really loving music in some kind of pure transcendent presence. I get there sometimes. Or I have. But not tonight. Tonight I’m barely listening to the music. Because not only am I overthinking it. I’m fucking writing about my overthinking on twitter.

But even if I were alone, I’d still be worried about whether my musical selection at the moment means I’m cool or not. I don’t know if I’m capable of putting on music without judging myself for it. Or applauding myself for it.

I wonder if he thinks the music is cool. I wonder if he thinks I’m cool. I wonder if he thinks I’m trying to look cool by putting on this music. I wonder if I am, in fact, trying to look cool. I wonder if I would have put something else on if I were alone?

Just put an album on in the car. I’m immediately self conscious about it. I’m not alone in this car. A lovely Nola native named Mike is driving. He’s been driving me to and from work on this movie. Mike’s not a judgey guy. Why can’t I just enjoy music in the presence of company?
